I"j<h1 id="lists">Lists</h1>

<p>Lists should be used to break up chunks of text to make it easier to read.</p>

<p>There are 3 types of list that can be used:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="#unordered-list">Unordered/Bulleted List</a></li>
  <li><a href="#ordered-list">Ordered/Numbered List</a></li>
  <li><a href="">Description List</a></li>
</ul>

<h2 id="unordered-list">Unordered list</h2>

<p>Introduce unordered lists with a lead-in line ending with a colon for context. Do not use full stops at the end of the item.</p>

<ul>
  <li>Short term (up to 6 weeks)</li>
  <li>Aids and minor adaptations</li>
  <li>Support services offered to carers</li>
</ul>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Short term (up to 6 weeks)&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Aids and minor adaptations&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Support services offered to carers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</code></pre></div></div>

<h2 id="ordered-list">Ordered list</h2>

<p>Use ordered lists when the order of the items is relevant.</p>

<p>Items should be complete sentences and end in a full stop.</p>

<ol>
  <li>Paying for care and support</li>
  <li>Care in a residential home</li>
  <li>Financial assessment explained</li>
</ol>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Paying for care and support&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Care in a residential home&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Financial assessment explained&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</code></pre></div></div>

<h2 id="content-to-be-published">Content to be published</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Description List</li>
</ul>
